column1: Our small businesses have been hit hard by the impact of #COVID19 and they need our support. Participate in #SmallBusinessSaturday and join me in shopping local!
We are so grateful to our health care heroes who have been on the frontlines working to create a vaccine for #COVID19. Your dedication represents the very best of American ingenuity. 🇺🇸

Vice President @Mike_Pence has done a great job leading the #COVID19 task force. Now more than ever we need him and President @realDonaldTrump working together to get our economy on track again. #KAG2020 #VPDebate

Kamala Harris and the Democrats were so focused on impeachment that they wasted valuable time in the response to #COVID19. @realDonaldTrump & @Mike_Pence on the other hand took early action that saved the lives of countless Americans. #VPDebate
We need a leader like President @realDonaldTrump who has the business experience necessary to keep our economy going and recover from #COVID19. #Debates2020
In the wake of #COVID19 it is vitally important that we focus on getting our economy fully reopen and back on track.
Tennesseans are resilient - despite the economic toll that COVID-19 has taken on our country Tennessee is expected to outpace other states on economic recovery.  https://t.co/3flP66wCKe
Happy Labor Day! I hope you'll join me in thanking the frontline heroes who have worked tirelessly every day throughout COVID-19. https://t.co/YsArhJROAR
In the wake of #COVID19 it is vitally important that we focus on getting our economy fully reopen and back on track.
Even during #COVID19 Democrats are pushing for Medicare-For-All and the Green New Deal. This would add billions of unnecessary dollars to our national debt.
The Tennessee economy is driven by our small businesses who are hurting right now due to #COVID19. I am fighting every day to make sure they are given the resources they need to thrive again.
On National Nurses Day we honor all of the nurses who are working tirelessly on the frontlines of #COVID19. We appreciate all that you do. https://t.co/LoOBXiv51W

We must remember that we are #InItTogether to keep our communities strong during #COVID19. To find resources on volunteer opportunities and ways to support your neighbors during this time click below👇  https://t.co/cDmkQ1rU19
To help prevent the spread of #COVID19 we must do our part in following @CDCgov 's best practices to stop community outbreak in our state. https://t.co/lxaLwmkJaY

Have a question about #COVID19? You can find answers and get information on resources in your area by reaching out to The Tennessee Coronavirus Hotline. The hotline is available every day from 10:00 AM - 10:00 PM CT. https://t.co/1KO9ieTnh2
We must remember that during this time of social distancing we are #InItTogether. By working together we will come out on the other side of #COVID19 stronger than before!

The COVID-19 Unified Command will be crucial as our TN leaders continue efforts to stop the spread of coronavirus help our local businesses & strengthen our supply chains. @mcwhorters is the right person for this job & I look forward to working with him.
As we work together to stop the spread of coronavirus I urge you to follow all guidance from President @realDonaldTrump and the @CDCgov: https://t.co/gxmJojlTVY

President @realDonaldTrump made the right decision when he set travel restrictions and he is continuing to do what it takes to protect the American people. I support the President and am proud of his swift action to contain the impact of the coronavirus in the U.S.
